comments[29]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T19:24:59.262Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: actively shrinking the enforced CLI/MCP private-core baseline through the pm-3mna schema ownership extraction. This run will not claim the capstone complete unless the baseline truly reaches zero."
  "2026-07-14T19:41:00.327Z",codex-gpt5,"Progress evidence: removed all 17 schema-domain private-core edges previously attributed to src/cli/commands/schema.ts. The boundary ratchet passes with zero new imports; the broader baseline remains intentionally open and is not claimed complete."
  "2026-07-14T20:19:49.227Z",codex-root,"Final branch evidence: removed all 17 private-core imports formerly owned by src/cli/commands/schema.ts and deleted that stale baseline block. pnpm quality:static passes with no new private imports, no stale baseline entries, zero unsupported dynamic imports, 100% docstrings, and token budgets green. The repository-wide boundary baseline is not yet zero, so this capstone returns to open for the remaining command families."
  "2026-07-14T22:56:38.841Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-15: actively removing config/profile/init baseline entries as part of pm-3mna. This capstone will close only if the full repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise exact progress will be recorded and it will return to open."
  "2026-07-14T23:31:17.495Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence 2026-07-15: moved config, profile, init, init-agent-guidance, and templates into SDK ownership and removed their 54 grandfathered CLI-to-core edges. The static boundary gate reports actual_edge_count=642, baseline_edge_count=642, zero new imports, zero stale entries, and zero unsupported dynamic imports. Because 642 edges remain and the acceptance criterion requires zero plus deletion of the baseline, this capstone is deliberately returning to open rather than being falsely closed."
  "2026-07-15T01:03:56.201Z",codex-root,"Review-driven implementation evidence 2026-07-15: promoted the complete extension lifecycle engine and cohesive helpers from src/cli/commands/extension* into src/sdk/extension*, kept only thin CLI compatibility re-exports, and made SDK runtime/init consume the SDK implementation directly. This removed 45 additional grandfathered private-core edges: static quality reports actual_edge_count=597, baseline_edge_count=597, zero new/stale/dynamic violations. Suppression pruning reduced the mandatory budget 170 -> 167. Final all-source verification passes 291 files / 5,713 tests at exact 100%: 36,940 statements, 26,521 branches, 7,450 functions, 36,055 lines. The capstone remains incomplete because 597 edges remain, so it is returning to open."
  "2026-07-15T01:25:55.511Z",codex-root,"Second-head CodeQL evidence: accepted the polynomial-regex finding introduced by relocating the extension helper into the PR diff. Replaced the overlapping anchored alternation with two linear anchored trims and added a 20,004-character adversarial hyphen-run regression. Focused extension tests pass 125/125; strict lint/static quality pass; final all-source coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,713 tests. Thread reacted to, replied inline, and resolved."
  "2026-07-15T02:24:58.381Z",codex-root,"Third-head review evidence: replaced per-destination extension install locking with one scope-wide transaction lock carrying a UUID owner token; stale and final cleanup re-read ownership before removal, and regressions prove cross-destination serialization, invalid/stale-owner refusal, replacement-owner preservation, and owner-write cleanup. Install activation now requires explicit runtime status ok. Executable aliases moved into SDK contracts so SDK scaffolding has no reverse CLI dependency. Directory normalization uses linear index scans, eliminating both CodeQL regex findings. Focused extension/bootstrap tests pass 216/216; repository verification passes 291 files / 5,717 tests at exact 100%: 36,962 statements, 26,531 branches, 7,453 functions, 36,077 lines. Typecheck, lint, duplicates, static/docstring/package/token gates pass; suppression budget improved 167 -> 166. Temp-directory package-first dogfood passed 88 real CLI/SDK/package commands."
  "2026-07-15T03:10:16.485Z",codex-root,"Fourth-head CodeRabbit evidence: accepted the active-lock-expiry finding. Scope locks now run an owner-token-bound lease heartbeat at one-third of the stale interval; every tick re-reads current ownership before refreshing mtime, stop is an async barrier before final release, and heartbeat I/O failure remains best-effort without aborting the install. Regressions prove a transaction running beyond stale_ms retains exclusivity, replacement owners are never heartbeated or removed, and failed heartbeats do not break installs. Focused extension tests pass 124/124; full verification passes 291 files / 5,719 tests at exact 100%: 36,977 statements, 26,535 branches, 7,458 functions, 36,092 lines. Typecheck, strict quality gates, and 88-command temp-directory dogfood pass."
  "2026-07-15T06:48:50.369Z",codex-root,"Implementation scope 2026-07-15: actively remove governance/health/gc CLI-to-core allowances through SDK ownership. This capstone closes only if the complete repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise it will return to open with exact remaining-edge evidence."
  "2026-07-15T07:26:14.575Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence: this bundle removes the CLI-owned validate/health/gc implementations and 59 private import edges from the ratchet. The allowed baseline is now 62 entries, so the zero-baseline capstone is intentionally not closed; static quality proves no new reverse edges."
  "2026-07-16T05:59:56.129Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Implementation start 2026-07-16: actively remove the complete execution/diagnostics family from the CLI-to-core baseline through SDK ownership. The capstone will close only if the repository baseline reaches zero; otherwise exact remaining source/edge counts will be recorded and the item returned to open."
  "2026-07-16T06:10:46.707Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Boundary checkpoint: the same behavior now resolves through SDK ownership, reducing the ratcheted baseline from 62 sources / 538 import edges to 54 sources / 466 edges. The zero-boundary capstone remains incomplete and will return to open after this active burn-down."
  "2026-07-16T06:41:40.968Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Release-grade evidence: exact coverage and local gates pass after boundary burn-down; transient Sentry PM-CLI-10 was traced to an intermediate local module relocation, while the final packed package installs and executes guide-shell successfully. This capstone still remains open solely because 54 source entries / 466 edges remain."
  "2026-07-16T06:56:15.098Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Duplicate/lineage check: all-status searches found closed pm-rjqr as the completed public query-wrapper feature and no active duplicate implementation-ownership item. The zero-boundary capstone owns this concrete SDK search promotion; closed lineage remains closed."
  "2026-07-16T07:04:07.920Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Greptile P2 addressed: promoted list + search and their cohesive query helpers into src/sdk/query, removed the SDK eval reverse dependency, and removed 54 additional grandfathered edges. Static quality passes with 51 source entries / 412 edges remaining, zero new/stale/dynamic boundary violations."
  "2026-07-16T07:35:08.461Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Final local verification after query promotion: pnpm release:gates passed; 292 files / 5,738 tests at exact 100% coverage (37,232 statements, 26,504 branches, 7,533 functions, 36,335 lines); static/docstring/package/token/security/version gates passed; 12-package packed npx smoke and 88-command temp dogfood passed. Installed tarball proof in /tmp/pm-sdk-query-proof-4WKmtO returned list=1, search=1, eval nDCG=1 through public SDK exports."
  "2026-07-16T07:45:05.670Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Exact-head Greptile pre-push review 255811b3-17cc-4808-8b44-407ed3aff65b completed at confidence 5/5 with no review comments. Its two cosmetic observations were verified as branch-local: removed npm-generated legacy package.json main/directories fields and updated the promoted SDK query parser module description. Build, 100% docstring/static quality, package boundary, and token-budget gates pass after cleanup. The capstone remains incomplete only because 51 source entries / 412 import edges remain."
  "2026-07-16T08:49:58.774Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"PR #573 review-hardening evidence: accepted and fixed projection honesty, blank numeric validation, complete highlight windows, internal search-flag stripping, safe unknown-error handling, missing-file stats reads, case-normalized duplicate keys, null-prototype user maps, strict numeric assertions, metadata-complete path deduplication, shell-wrapped recursion guards, positive/fractional timeout contracts, own-property JSON lookup, and project/global extension mismatch detection. Governance and update-many callers now explicitly request full list records. Two suggestions were intentionally rejected: public pm tracker links remain required by repository documentation policy, and unbounded Promise.all tracker reads would create unsafe fanout. Full release:gates passes: 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100% (37,260 statements, 26,520 branches, 7,536 functions, 36,360 lines), 100% docstrings, static/package-boundary/token/version/security gates, 12-package packed smoke, and 88-command temp dogfood. Boundary ratchet is clean at 51 source allowances / 412 edges with zero new, stale, or dynamic violations; therefore the zero-boundary capstone returns to open."
  "2026-07-16T09:22:45.630Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"PR #573 exact-head bot follow-up: CI identified and pruned one stale ESLint suppression, lowering the mandatory ratchet 157 -> 156 across the gate, package script, and contract tests. DeepSource findings added purpose-specific docstrings to three governance projection/index helpers. CodeRabbit findings corrected the fractional run-timeout diagnostic and replaced the calendar-dependent 2030 list fixture with a runtime future date. Strict pnpm lint now passes with zero jscpd clones; static quality, 100% docstrings, package boundary, and token gates pass. Final exact coverage remains 292 files / 5,744 tests at 100/100/100/100 (37,260 statements, 26,520 branches, 7,536 functions, 36,360 lines). The new Gemini path-dedup comment was verified already resolved on head: buildLinkedTestKey includes normalized env_set, env_clear, pm_context_mode, shared_host_safe, and assertions for path tests."
  "2026-07-16T09:47:31.807Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"PR #573 analyzer closeout: queried DeepScan public API for defect 230772515 and removed the redundant !state.maxBufferExceeded condition proven constant after the early-return guard. Converted the three DeepSource-targeted governance helper comments to full multiline JSDoc so both repository and hosted analyzers recognize them. Strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token gates pass; focused execution/governance tests pass 60/60; final repository coverage remains 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-16T10:01:38.541Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"DeepSource compatibility follow-up: its own rule text permits documentation immediately inside a function declaration, so the three helper purpose comments now use that recognized placement without adding analyzer exclusions or weakening the repository 100% docstring gate. Full strict lint, zero-duplicate, static, package-boundary, and token gates pass."
  "2026-07-16T10:43:27.847Z",codex-root,"Exact-head hosted-review follow-up: replaced an unsafe linked-artifact cast with runtime structural validation and added a malformed-payload regression; converted the symlink escape regression to independent per-path assertions so neither project nor global reads can false-pass; documented all newly reported comments-audit helpers and reduced resolveCommentsAuditLimits complexity. Focused tests pass 136/136, strict lint passes with zero duplicates and 100% docstrings/static gates, and full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,267 statements, 26,519 branches, 7,538 functions, 36,366 lines)."
  "2026-07-16T11:02:06.124Z",codex-root,"DeepSource strict-gate closeout: exact run 8ceb9f45 exposed the final undocumented parseMode/buildCommentsAuditFilters helpers and medium-complexity comments-audit result shaping. Added purpose documentation, consolidated nullable filter projection, and simplified limit/export/result construction without suppressions or threshold changes. Focused governance tests pass 62/62; strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token gates pass with zero duplicates; full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,278 statements, 26,495 branches, 7,539 functions, 36,375 lines)."
  "2026-07-16T11:25:26.784Z",codex-root,"Final DeepSource threshold follow-up: documented dedupe-audit parseStatus and reduced resolveCommentsAuditLimits/runCommentsAudit cyclomatic complexity below the hosted medium-risk boundary by consolidating conflict evaluation and full-history result mutation. Focused governance tests pass 62/62; strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token gates pass with zero duplicates; full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,275 statements, 26,491 branches, 7,539 functions, 36,373 lines)."
  "2026-07-16T11:41:33.041Z",codex-root,"DeepSource serial-report prevention: documented every remaining private function declaration across the touched dedupe-audit, dedupe-merge, and governance runtime-utils modules using the hosted analyzer-compatible inside-body placement. No analyzer exclusions or threshold weakening were added. Focused governance tests pass 29/29; strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token gates pass with zero duplicates; the immediately preceding behavior head retains exact 292-file / 5,744-test 100/100/100/100 coverage."
  "2026-07-16T12:07:09.614Z",codex-root,"DeepSource analyzer-compatibility evidence: the repository ESM configuration was already correct, but hosted JS-0067 classified module-private function declarations as global-script declarations. Converted every private top-level helper in the four touched governance modules to lexical const arrow bindings while preserving all public exports and behavior, without exclusions, suppressions, or threshold weakening. Focused governance verification passes 71/71; strict lint, static quality, package boundary, token budget, and zero-duplicate gates pass; full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,311 statements, 26,491 branches, 7,539 functions, 36,409 lines). The capstone remains open because the repository boundary baseline is still 51 source entries / 412 edges."
  "2026-07-16T12:42:18.345Z",codex-root,"Exact-run hosted review remediation: fixed Greptile's valid count-only plus explicit zero-limit search finding so matching documents are still scored and counted, with a regression proving count=3/total=3/items=[] for limit=0. Refactored analyzer-visible governance complexity into reusable candidate-pair, grouping, merge-outcome, audit-decoration, and error/default primitives; removed changed export declarations that DeepSource misclassified as globals; preserved deterministic singleton/fallback behavior and added the missing undefined-options branch proof. No analyzer exclusions, suppressions, or threshold weakening were introduced. Focused tests pass 117/117; strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token and zero-duplicate gates pass; full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,312 statements, 26,450 branches, 7,562 functions, 36,405 lines). The capstone remains open at 51 sources / 412 edges."
  "2026-07-16T13:09:42.982Z",codex-root,"Third exact-run review evidence: accepted CodeRabbit's merge-integrity finding so any failed active-child reparent now prevents the duplicate from closing; expanded the mutation-failure regression with two blocked children plus a no-child duplicate that still exercises close failure. Rejected Gemini's canonical-check removal after the existing prefixless-id regression proved raw parse validation cannot detect aliases that resolve to the canonical record. Rejected its JSON-path consolidation finding as stale: only execution.ts defines those helpers on this head and traversal already uses own-property checks. DeepSource serial analysis had advanced into normalize.ts, so every changed private/public normalize implementation now uses documented lexical exports/bindings, closure backfill is table-driven, and plan application is factored into bounded-complexity primitives without suppressions. Focused tests pass 27/27; strict lint/static/docstring/boundary/token and zero-duplicate gates pass; full coverage passes 292 files / 5,744 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (37,344 statements, 26,444 branches, 7,571 functions, 36,433 lines). Capstone remains open at 51 sources / 412 edges."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T06:21:39.876Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#565 progress (2026-07-15): 54 obsolete CLI-to-core import-boundary allowances removed; pm-3mna slice shipped (SDK owns config/profile/init/agent-guidance/templates/extension + createPmCliProgram + renderPmCommand). Baseline scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json still holds ~60 source files (commands/*, main.ts, register-*, mcp/server.ts) — the zero target remains. With 3mna/4a7m/hib1/zwpp shipped, remaining prerequisite slices are pm-oxrw (governance/health) then pm-oslr (execution/diagnostics)."
learnings[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T20:19:49.944Z",codex-root,Boundary burn-down is strongest when the implementation itself moves to an SDK-owned module; deleting a baseline block without changing ownership would only hide the dependency direction.
  "2026-07-14T23:31:18.238Z",codex-root,Compatibility shims must remain locally referenced or be deleted after SDK promotion; the orphan-module gate correctly prevents dead presentation paths from surviving solely for tests.
  "2026-07-15T02:24:59.166Z",codex-root,Shared extension managed-state and settings mutations require scope-level serialization; destination-level locks protect copies but cannot protect shared snapshots. Persisted unique ownership must be re-read before stale reclaim and final release so an earlier installer cannot delete a replacement lock.
  "2026-07-15T03:10:17.167Z",codex-root,"A stale timeout is a lease duration, not an install duration: long-running owners must refresh liveness under the same persisted owner token, and cleanup must await any in-flight heartbeat before comparing and releasing ownership."
